<item>
            <title>[SOLR-17186] Streaming query breaks if token contains backtick</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/SOLR-17186</link>
                <project id="12310230" key="SOLR">Solr</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;Streaming searches break when the data contains the backtick character( ` ).&#160;&lt;br/&gt;
Eg:&lt;br/&gt;
&lt;a href=&quot;http://pidx.idcprodcert.loc:20000/solr/sharepointindex_036DE237-A69B-4E7E-929E-62C2AB7A7323_multinode/stream?expr=search(sharepointindex_036DE237-A69B-4E7E-929E-62C2AB7A7323_multinode,q=%22slevel_Url_8:Fotos%22,fl=%22contentid%22)&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;http://host-name:8983/solr/MyCollection/stream?expr=search(MyCollection,q=&quot;My_Field:Foto`s&quot;,fl=&quot;field1&quot;,qt=&quot;/export&quot;)&lt;/a&gt;&lt;br/&gt;
&#160;&lt;br/&gt;
Same search works fine if called directly with /export or /select&lt;br/&gt;
&#160;&lt;/p&gt;</description>
